The paper deals with secure communication in the presence of an eavesdropper, which is a common topic in the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of random scheduling and its implementation on wireless sensor networks, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of sleep mode to save energy, which is a topic in the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the overhead advantage of the proposed scheme, which is related to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
